text.section:
In setting the amount of a civil money penalty under this section, the Secretary shall consider, pursuant to guidelines set forth in regulations promulgated by the Secretary, the following factors:
The number, nature, and seriousness of the deficiencies;
The degree of risk to the health, life, or safety of the residents of the nursing home caused by the deficiency or deficiencies;
The efforts made by the nursing home to correct the deficiency or deficiencies;
Current federal guidelines for money penalties;
Whether the amount of the proposed civil money penalty will jeopardize the financial ability of the nursing home to continue operating as a nursing home; and
Such other factors as justice may require.
